oc:kn_2155514a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining driver categories for any environmental dataset" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keep the number of driver categories manageable, typically 3-5. Use domain knowledge to define categories based on physical meaning, not statistical convenience." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Too many categories dilute attribution signal; too few obscure individual driver effects." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6ac9f031 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After statistical grouping, during validation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Categories should be mutually exclusive and each variable should load on the expected component. Groupings must make physical sense." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overlap between categories confounds attribution; physical plausibility ensures interpretability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c04fce0f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When raw variables are correlated components of a single physical quantity" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Combine related sub-variables (e.g., shortwave + longwave radiation into net radiation) before attribution analysis." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Collinear variables within a category inflate dimensionality and distort R² decomposition." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d1ad88d6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Throughout the classification process" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always document your classification decisions so the rationale for grouping is transparent and reproducible." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Classification choices are subjective; documentation enables peer review and reproducibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d2189a1b a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assigning variables to categories" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Assumes that variables within the same physical category are correlated. If variables do not correlate as expected, reconsider the classification." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The entire framework depends on within-category correlation and between-category independence." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

